# EAS Build archive ignore — MUST live at the git repository root.
#
# EAS copies the archive starting from the git root (this dir), NOT from the
# app subdirectory you run `eas build` in. Without this file, a build uploads
# the ENTIRE monorepo (all apps + a ~40 MB .git) instead of just the app.
#
# Both EAS apps here (apps/nuru, apps/mobile) are standalone Expo apps with no
# @mcloud/* / workspace deps, so we ignore everything and re-include only those
# two app dirs (minus their heavy/generated subdirs). A build from either app
# carries both apps' source, which is tiny (~1 MB each) and harmless.
#
# Adding a NEW EAS app? Add a matching `!apps/<name>` + `!apps/<name>/**` pair
# and its heavy-dir excludes below.

# Ignore everything by default...
/*
apps/*

# ...then re-include only the EAS app dirs.
!apps
!apps/nuru
!apps/nuru/**
!apps/mobile
!apps/mobile/**

# Even within the apps, never upload heavy/generated dirs.
apps/nuru/node_modules
apps/nuru/dist
apps/nuru/web-build
apps/nuru/.expo
apps/nuru/.expo-shared
apps/nuru/android
apps/nuru/ios
apps/nuru/.kotlin
apps/nuru/*.aab
apps/nuru/*.apk

apps/mobile/node_modules
apps/mobile/dist
apps/mobile/web-build
apps/mobile/.expo
apps/mobile/.expo-shared
apps/mobile/android
apps/mobile/ios
apps/mobile/.kotlin
apps/mobile/*.aab
apps/mobile/*.apk
